==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seashore
<hw>Sea"shore`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
coast of the sea; the land that lies adjacent to the sea or
ocean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>All the ground between the ordinary
high-water and low-water marks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seasick</ent>⟦br⟧
